<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1602,1690]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,302,1602,1626]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Ecology</emphasis>
. Lowland, montane, subalpine. Epigean-arboreal. Wet forests (beech, podocarp, broadleaf). Shaded ground. Nocturnal; active at night on mossy logs and trees; hides during the day under logs, fallen branches, and the loose bark of fallen trees. Gregarious.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1441,1729,1786]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,296,1729,1753]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: September–March, May–August. Tenerals: February–March, August. Predacious (based on mouthpart morphology).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1825,1850]" box="[192,1440,1825,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,416,1825,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Subapterous (incapable of flight). Fast runner. Occasional climber on logs and trees.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1889,1914]" box="[192,1440,1889,1914]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,489,1889,1913]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Collecting techniques</emphasis>
. Lifting logs, fallen branches, and the loose bark of fallen trees; pitfall trapping.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
