<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,322,506]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,322,346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
. Sharp described 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Larochelle and Lariviere" authorityYear="2007" box="[532,644,322,346]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helmsi">
<emphasis box="[532,644,322,346]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Z. helmsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a pair of specimens, one of which (a male) is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[227,341,354,378]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The second specimen (a female) is considered to be a 
<typeStatus box="[1011,1182,354,378]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">paralectotype</typeStatus>
. These type designations are made to preserve stability of nomenclature in the future. As stated in Broun’s description, the male 
<typeStatus box="[259,364,418,442]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="(BMNH)" baseAuthorityName="BMNH" box="[399,639,418,442]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labralis">
<emphasis box="[399,527,418,442]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Z. labralis</emphasis>
(BMNH)
</taxonomicName>
only has four setiferous punctures on the labrum; this represents an anomaly. In all other material seen, the labrum displays six setiferous punctures. Examination of the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[330,458,482,506]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labralis">
<emphasis box="[330,458,482,506]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Z. labralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed it to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Larochelle and Lariviere" authorityYear="2007" box="[872,986,482,506]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helmsi">
<emphasis box="[872,986,482,506]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Z. helmsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
